						</tr>
					</table>

				<p>Does this sentence express this fact? That is that Michelle Obama has a nationality of United States? In this example, the correct answer is <strong>no</strong>. While we know that Michelle Obama is a U.S. citizen, this sentence does not imply that. This sentence only tells us that she was speaking at a convention of some U.S. based organization.</p>

